  "text": "The treatment of pubic osteomyelitis is based on the administration of antimicrobial agents and surgical therapy. Because of the rich blood flow in the pelvis, pubic osteomyelitis often shows spectacular improvement in inflammation with only intravenous antimicrobial therapy. Busto et al. reported that they reviewed seven patients with osteomyelitis of the pubis. Patients received antibiotic treatment for a minimum of three weeks and a maximum of 12 weeks. The response to antibiotic therapy was good in all patients and none required surgical debridement [CITATION_1] .",
